@startuml c4-jotp-07h-sequence-atomic-write
title JOTP - Atomic Write Sequence Diagram (Dual-Write Problem Solution)

participant "Process\nHandler" as Handler
participant "AtomicStateWriter" as Writer
participant "RocksDBBackend" as Backend
participant "WriteBatch" as Batch
participant "RocksDB\nEngine" as Engine
participant "WAL\n(Write-Ahead Log)" as WAL
participant "SSTable\n(Disk)" as SSTable
participant "Column Family:\nstate" as StateCF
participant "Column Family:\nack" as AckCF

== The Dual-Write Problem ==

note over Handler, AckCF #pink
  WITHOUT ATOMIC WRITES:
  1. Write state -> SUCCESS
  2. JVM CRASH!
  3. ACK never written
  4. On recovery: message replayed as unprocessed
  5. DUPLICATE PROCESSING IS INEVITABLE
end note

== Atomic Write Solution ==

Handler ->> Handler: process message
note over Handler
  newState = handle(state, msg)
  seqNum = msg.sequenceNumber()
end note

Handler ->> Writer: writeAtomic(key, newState, seqNum)
activate Writer

Writer ->> Writer: codec.encode(newState)
Writer ->> Writer: ackBytes = String.valueOf(seqNum)

Writer ->> Backend: writeAtomic(key, stateBytes, ackBytes)
activate Backend

Backend ->> Batch: new WriteBatch()
activate Batch

note over Batch
  Single batch containing
  BOTH writes:
  1. State update
  2. ACK marker
end note

Batch ->> StateCF: batch.put(key, stateBytes)
Batch ->> AckCF: batch.put(ackKey, ackBytes)

Backend ->> Engine: db.write(syncWriteOptions, batch)
activate Engine

note over Engine
  WriteOptions.setSync(true)
  CRITICAL for crash safety
end note

Engine ->> WAL: append batch entry
activate WAL

note over WAL
  Write-Ahead Log ensures:
  - All or nothing semantics
  - Atomic persistence guarantee
  - Crash recovery support
end note

WAL ->> SSTable: eventually compacted
activate SSTable
SSTable -->> WAL: persisted
deactivate SSTable

WAL -->> Engine: fsync complete
deactivate WAL

Engine -->> Backend: success
deactivate Engine

deactivate Batch
Backend -->> Writer: committed
deactivate Backend

Writer -->> Handler: success
deactivate Writer

note over Handler, AckCF #lightgreen
  WITH ATOMIC WRITES:
  1. WriteBatch contains state + ACK
  2. If JVM crashes mid-write:
     - WAL ensures both are persisted, OR
     - Neither is persisted
  3. On recovery:
     - If state.seq == ack.seq: consistent
     - If mismatch: use ACK as truth
  4. IDEMPOTENT RECOVERY GUARANTEED
end note

== Crash During Write ==

alt JVM crashes after batch.put(state) but before db.write()

    note over Engine #red
      JVM CRASH!
      Batch never submitted
    end note

    note over WAL
      WAL is empty for this transaction
      No partial writes visible
    end note

    == Recovery ==

    Backend ->> Backend: getAckSequence(key)
    Backend -->> Backend: Optional.empty()

    Backend ->> Backend: load(key)
    Backend -->> Backend: Optional.empty()

    note over Backend
      Neither state nor ACK exist
      Clean state - start fresh
    end note

else JVM crashes during db.write() after WAL append

    note over Engine #red
      JVM CRASH!
      After WAL, before return
    end note

    == Recovery ==

    Backend ->> Backend: getAckSequence(key)
    Backend -->> Backend: Optional.of(42)

    Backend ->> Backend: load(key)
    Backend -->> Backend: state with seq=42

    Backend ->> Backend: verify state.seq == ack.seq
    note over Backend
      42 == 42 -> CONSISTENT
      Recovery succeeds
    end note

end

@enduml
